{
  "stem": "12255.2",
  "chunk_idx": 7,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 10.8,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 37,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "And B, people who were coming from deep in Russia through Germany, through Belgium-- through Berlin, rather-- through Berlin, into Germany, into the British zone, particularly.",
      "word_count": 26
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 37,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "And from there, filtering down to Italy or over the borders into France to Marseille, and getting on what was called Aliyah Bet, the illegal-- the illegal immigration into Israel.",
      "word_count": 30
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 38,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "And there were many, many Israelis from the Jewish Brigade who, for quite some time, were stationed in Belgium who were roving around the country helping these people in many ways.",
      "word_count": 31
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 39,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "All over Germany, and penetrating into Russia and all over.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 39,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "It is really remarkable what those boys did in bringing and encouraging people to come through.",
      "word_count": 16
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 39,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "And it was here that I had a very unusual experience.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 39,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "Shall I tell you about it now?",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 40,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "My office was in a house in Germany, in Iserlohn, where all the, the-- where the senior chaplains of each religion had their offices.",
      "word_count": 24
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 40,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "And the senior chaplain of us all, the official officer in charge of the chaplains, was the, the Protestant bishop, whatever he was.",
      "word_count": 23
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 40,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "And I had my office on the ground floor.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 41,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "One day, I come to my office, and I find a note from a Christian chaplain saying that there were a group of Jews in a camp at-- and gave me the map references.",
      "word_count": 34
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 41,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "I couldn't understand this, because when I looked it up, it looked like an internment camp for Nazi criminals.",
      "word_count": 19
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 41,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "How can Jews get there?",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 41,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "So together with my faithful batman, Abey, we started off.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 41,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "We went to this place.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 41,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "And when we got there, I entered the camp and reported to the adjutant's office, and-- a major.",
      "word_count": 18
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 41,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "And he said, padre, I shouldn't be doing this, but I asked the chaplain to let you know.",
      "word_count": 18
    }
  ],
